nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|When you play kickback, RKCB is one suit higher than the trump suit. That means since clubs are trump, 4@D would be RKCB. The convention is a little advanced for most players. But even if you don't play full Kickback, you definitely should play it when hearts are trump.|
PG| ***** 58 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|You should bid 4@S rather than 4NT as RKCB because then you can always do the queen ask even if the response is the 2nd step. If hearts are trump and you bid 4NT as RKCB then if partner responds 5@C, you can do the queen ask of 5@D without going past 5@H. |
PG| ***** 59 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, if partner responds 5@D, you can't do the queen ask (which would be 5@S) without going past 5@H and you might not want to do that. So if you play 4@S as RKCB for hearts then whether partner responds 4NT or 5@C you can do the queen ask without going past 5@H. |
PG| ***** 60 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|BTW, if you play Kickback, most play 0314 instead of the rather silly 1430 that most play. |
