nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Here admitedly the lower suit clubs is stronger than the higher suit diamonds. But the diamonds do have 2 honors plus another intermediate. So they are not that weak. As to my 4@S bid, I had close to a "self sufficient" suit. |
PG| ***** 94 ***** |


nt|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|A self sufficient suit is one that is likely to have one loser opposite a singleton. Here if North had a small singleton than I might have 2 losers if spades were 4-2. But if North had the king, as he did I have no losers and the 10 gives me only one spade loser. So that's why I felt 4@S was justified.
|
